# Custom Truck Rear Lighting Harness
Professional 12V Combined Brake / Turn / Tail System

---

## 📌 Overview

This repository documents the design, architecture, schematics, and implementation details of a custom-built rear lighting harness for a 12V negative-ground truck system.

System includes:

- Combined Brake + Turn rear lights (Red)
- Tail / Running light circuit
- Optional auxiliary clear turn indicators
- Dedicated ground bus architecture
- Under-dash / engine-bay mounted fuse block
- Serviceable, modular harness layout

Designed for durability, serviceability, and professional-grade reliability.

---

## ⚙️ System Specifications

| Parameter | Value |
|------------|--------|
| System Voltage | 12V DC Negative Ground |
| Main Feed Wire | 10–12 AWG TXL |
| Branch Circuits | 14–16 AWG TXL |
| Fuse Block Location | Under Dash / Engine Bay |
| Protection | ATC/ATO Blade Fuses |
| Grounding Strategy | Dedicated Ground Bus |

---

## 🔌 Circuit Architecture

### Power Distribution
- 30A Main Inline Fuse (near battery)
- 10A Tail Circuit
- 15A Brake Circuit
- 15A Turn Circuit

### Functional Logic
- Brake switch feeds turn signal switch
- Flasher feeds turn signal switch
- Turn switch distributes to left/right rear outputs
- Brown wire supplies tail lights
- Dedicated 12 AWG ground return to battery

